{"title":"Magnetic Resonance Elastography","markdown":{"headingText":"Magnetic Resonance Elastography","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":["scrollable"],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"{{< include macros.qmd >}}\n\n\n\nAim: Remote palpation by shear waves, i.e. tomographic quantification of shear modulus of biological tissue.\n\n\n\n\n::: columns\n::: {.column width=\"60%\"}\n\n- Induce excitation at a given frequency (e.g. 50Hz).\n\n\n- Measure (complex) displacements $\\blue{\\bfu(\\bfx)}$ via MRI (Motion encoding gradient).\n\n\n\n- Invert displacements to find \nshear modulus $\\red{G(\\bfx)}$: viscoelastic properties\n\n:::\n::: {.column width=\"40%\"}\n\n\n![](Figs_for_MRE/Set1.png){width=95%}\n\n\n\n\n\n:::\n\n:::\n\n\nA: T1/T2 weighted} B: $\\vert \\bfu(\\bfx)\\vert$ C: $\\vert G(\\bfx)\\vert\\qquad$. \n\n![](Figs_for_MRE/Set2.png){width=100%}\n\nImages From: Tan CH, Venkatesh SK. MRE and Other Magnetic Resonance Imaging Techniques in Chronic Liver Disease: Current Status and Future Directions.  Gut and Liver 2016;10:672-686\n\n\n\n## Forward/Inverse Problem in MRE {.scrollable}\n\n::: callout-note\n\n## Forward Model\n\nTime-harmonic isotropic linear viscoelastic equations\n$$\n\\rho \\omega^2 \\blue{\\bfu} +\\nabla \\cdot \\big[ \\red{G} (\\nabla \\blue{\\bfu} +(\\nabla \\blue{\\bfu})^{T})\\big]+\\nabla (\\red{\\lambda} \\nabla \\cdot \\blue{\\bfu})=\\mathbf{0},\\qquad \\text{in}~ \\Omega,\n$$\n:::\n\n- Known quantities:  $\\omega$ (frequency) and $\\rho\\approx 10^{3}\\text{kg}/\\text{m}^3$.  \\\\\n\n- Unknown quantities: BCs, $\\lambda(\\bfx)$ and $G(\\bfx)$\n\n- Measured quantities (via MRI):  $\\bfu_{M}\\equiv (\\bfu(\\bfx_{1}),\\dots,\\bfu(\\bfx_{M}))$\n\n\n\n::: callout-important\n\n## Inverse Problem\n\nFind the shear modulus $G(\\bfx)=G_{s}(\\bfx)+iG_{l}(\\bfx),$ given measurements of  $\\bfu_{M}\\equiv (\\bfu(\\bfx_{1}),\\dots,\\bfu(\\bfx_{M}))$.\n\n:::\n\n$\\red{G_{s}(\\bfx)}$: storage modulus. $\\red{G_{l}(\\bfx)}$: loss modulus. \n\n\n## Characterisation: \n\n\n\n![](Figs_for_MRE/for_talk1.png){width=100%}\n\n\n::: backhub\n↩ <a href=\"index.html\">Volver al inicio</a>\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"clean-revealjs":{"identifier":{"display-name":"RevealJS","target-format":"clean-revealjs","base-format":"revealjs","extension-name":"clean"},"execute":{"fig-width":10,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":false,"output":true,"warning":false,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":false,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":true,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":["_extensions/clean/mathjax-config.js"],"shortcodes":[]},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","html-math-method":{"method":"mathjax","url":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@4/tex-mml-chtml.js"},"slide-level":2,"to":"revealjs","include-before-body":[{"text":"<script src=\"mathjax-config.js\"></script>\n"}],"filters":[],"css":["styles.css"],"self-contained":false,"output-file":"app-mre.html"},"language":{"toc-title-document":"Table of contents","toc-title-website":"On this page","